06:23.786 --> 06:28.032
flyers. And there were really sort of only three 
places on campus where you could put, which were

06:29.074 --> 06:38.026
places in which they would allow you to put 
campaign signs. And so by the time I bought the

06:38.868 --> 06:41.271
plywood and the paint, to do my sign over by Kruger 
Dunn, which caught all the guys and gals headed

06:42.145 --> 06:52.476
from the court area kind of toward the Animal 
Science Committee and then down toward the

06:42.145 --> 06:52.476
Engineering Department. One over by Sabisa, 
which was kind of to catch the kids on the north side

06:52.496 --> 06:59.543
of campus, and one right by the MSC. That $100 went 
away real fast. We didn't have websites like the

07:02.366 --> 07:11.376
kids can do now, which I thought was quite 
interesting during one of the most recent student

07:02.366 --> 07:11.376
body president campaigns. And Raj tried 
diligently to get me to go door to door and I did it

07:12.183 --> 07:20.879
one afternoon for about four doors and I said, I'm 
not going to do this. I'm going to do what I can to get

07:21.600 --> 07:25.687
my message out and hopefully this is going to work. 
